# Prisma Rules

## Schema Conventions

```prisma
// All models use uuid primary keys
model User {
  id        String     @id @default(uuid())
  email     String     @unique
  name      String
  role      UserRole   @default(USER)
  status    UserStatus @default(ACTIVE)
  password  String
  createdAt DateTime   @default(now())
  updatedAt DateTime   @updatedAt
  deletedAt DateTime?

  profile   Profile?
  orders    Order[]

  @@index([email])
  @@index([role])
  @@index([status])
  @@index([createdAt])
  @@map("users")
}
```

---

## Naming Conventions in Schema

- Model names: PascalCase singular (`User`, `Order`, `ProductCategory`)
- Table names: snake_case plural via `@@map` (`users`, `orders`, `product_categories`)
- Field names: camelCase in Prisma (`createdAt`), mapped to snake_case in DB (`created_at`)
- Foreign keys: `userId`, `orderId`, `productId` (camelCase, with `@relation`)

```prisma
model Order {
  id        String   @id @default(uuid())
  userId    String
  user      User     @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
  total     Decimal  @db.Decimal(10, 2)
  status    OrderStatus @default(PENDING)
  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt

  @@index([userId])
  @@index([status])
  @@map("orders")
}
```

