## Prisma Middleware / Extensions

Use Prisma middleware for cross-cutting concerns like soft-delete filtering:

```ts
this.prisma.$use(async (params, next) => {
  if (params.model === 'Order' && params.action === 'findMany') {
    params.args.where = { ...params.args.where, deletedAt: null };
  }
  return next(params);
});
```

---

## Prisma Enums

Define enums in schema and import in TypeScript:

```prisma
enum UserRole {
  SUPER_ADMIN
  ADMIN
  USER
}
```

```ts
import { UserRole } from '@prisma/client';
```

Never redefine enums in TypeScript — import from `@prisma/client` directly.

---

## Rules

- All models have `id` (uuid), `createdAt`, `updatedAt`
- All models use `@@map` for snake_case table names
- All foreign keys have `@@index`
- All enum values defined in Prisma schema (not repeated in TS)
- Never use `Int` auto-increment IDs — always uuid
- Always use `@db.Decimal` for monetary values — never `Float`
- Use `@@unique` for compound uniqueness constraints

---

## Forbidden

❌ Auto-increment integer primary keys
❌ `Float` for monetary/financial values — use `Decimal`
❌ Missing `@@map` table name mappings
❌ Missing indexes on foreign keys
❌ Redefining Prisma enums in TypeScript
❌ `any` in Prisma input types
❌ Untyped `data` objects in create/update calls
